   Via ferrata de la Grande Fistoire
   Via ferrata de la Grande Fistoire
   4.8
   powered by Google
   Jasper
   Jasper
   07:26 08 Aug 19
   Nice via ferrata. We climbed the whole route in about 2.15h. Some parts
   are steep and ask some strengh of the arms. After reaching the top you
   have to climb down to reach the bridge.
   Kristina Rapson
   Kristina Rapson
   12:49 03 Jan 19
   This via ferrata has 3 great zip lines at the end. The views are
   beautiful. Be prepared to climb down backwards though... Once you get
   over the top, you have to go back down the other side. I was not
   prepared for this, and found that part to be very difficult. I would
   not suggest this one for beginners or young children.
   Edward Hastrop
   Edward Hastrop
   07:07 28 Mar 18
   More challenging than expected, it is overhung in parts but very well
   equipped. The route feels varied with traverses, climbs, corners etc.
   Feels like an achievement to get to the top, then the fun start with a
   long bridge, optional rope bridge and steep climb. The highlights has
   to be the three long zipwires to get down culminating in a 220m zip.
   Just make sure you stick the landing!
   Matt Hinkley
   Matt Hinkley
   06:47 26 Sep 17
   Fabulous Via Ferrata.
   Pauline Exton
   Pauline Exton
   12:08 01 Sep 17
   What a great experience! I have no background in rock climbing, but
   thanks to our guide Marianne Mougey, I felt comfortable the whole time!
   It was a great experience filled with adrenalin and stunning views, I
   definitely recommend it!!
   Michał Marschall
   Michał Marschall
   22:39 23 Oct 16
   Quite exhausting via ferrata, but wonderful views.
   Asad Uzzaman
   Asad Uzzaman
   21:37 04 Oct 16
   People who love adventure this is place for do it. Adventurer people
   will like it that's i can guaranty!
